<def f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/widgets/kernel/qwidget.cpp' l='2531' ll='2535' type='void QWidget::setScreen(QScreen * screen)'/>
<doc f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/widgets/kernel/qwidget.cpp' l='2519'>/*!
    Sets the screen on which the widget should be shown to \a screen.

    Setting the screen only makes sense for windows. If necessary, the widget&apos;s
    window will get recreated on \a screen.

    \note If the screen is part of a virtual desktop of multiple screens,
    the window will not move automatically to \a screen. To place the
    window relative to the screen, use the screen&apos;s topLeft() position.

    \sa QWindow::setScreen()
*/</doc>
